{
  "text": "Diverse studies have been conducted investigating the functions and thickness of Tra affecting lumbar stabilization and balance. It has been shown that the thickness of Tra increases with lumbar stabilization exercises [CITATION_1] , and some studies have indicated that dynamic balance can also be improved by lumbar stabilization exercises [CITATION_2] . Tra has been studied using ultrasonic imaging to measure, changes in the thickness of Tra after Pilates exercises, methods have been used to activate Tra [CITATION_3] . It has been demonstrated that subjects with low back pain have weaker Tra contractile force using ultrasonic imaging [CITATION_4] , and changes in the thickness of Tra in various sitting positions have also been measured using ultrasonic imaging [CITATION_5] .",
